{"word":"Σαλώμη","slug":"Σαλώμη","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Σαλώμη, ης, ἡ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ etym.\">etym.</a> uncertain] <b>Salome,</b> a follower and benefactor of Jesus <b><a href='B:480 15:40'>Mk 15:40</a>; <a href='B:480 16:1'>16:1</a>.</b> Not to be confused with the daughter of Herodius, unnamed <a href='B:480 6:22'>Mk 6:22ff</a>; <a href='B:470 14:6'>Mt 14:6ff</a>. <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:σαλπιστής\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:Σαμάρεια\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}